Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and finely dice @red onion{1%unit}(diced). Open package of @ground turkey{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

Set aside 2 TBSP onion (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{a large drizzle} in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken, @blackening spice{1%tablespoon}, remaining onion, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

While chicken cooks, finely dice @tomato{1%unit}(diced). Zest and quarter @lime{1%unit}(zested and quartered).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine tomato, juice from one lime wedge (two lime wedges for 4), and 1 TBSP reserved onion (3 TBSP for 4 servings); add more onion to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, juice from one lime wedge (two lime wedges for 4 servings), and lime zest to taste. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches drizzling consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Place @flour tortillas{2%unit} on a clean work surface. Evenly sprinkle @pepper jack cheese{1/2%cup} and @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup} onto one half of each tortilla. Top cheese with filling, then fold tortillas in half to create quesadillas.

Heat a drizzle of oil and @butter{1%tbsp} in #pan used for filling{} over medium-high heat. Working in batches, add quesadillas and cook until golden brown on the first side, ~{1-2%minutes}. Flip and cook ~{1%minute} more.

Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

Transfer quesadillas to a #cutting board{}; slice into thirds and divide between plates. Serve with salsa, lime crema, and @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} to taste. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Ground Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.